<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">The LocalGov Drupal homepage</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  LocalGov Drupal is designed specifically for UK councils. The homepage follows
  GOV.UK design patterns that residents expect from government services.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
  <strong>To view the homepage:</strong> Click on your site name in the admin toolbar,
  or visit the DrupalUrl without any path.
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Key areas to explore</h3>

<div class="ndx-explore-grid">
  <div class="ndx-explore-card">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">
      <span class="ndx-explore-card__number">1</span>
      Main navigation
    </h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      The top menu provides access to key service areas: Waste & Recycling,
      Planning, Council Tax, Housing, and more. This matches how residents
      typically look for council services.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-explore-card">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">
      <span class="ndx-explore-card__number">2</span>
      Service cards
    </h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      The homepage displays prominent service cards for frequently accessed
      services. Each card links to a service landing page with detailed information.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-explore-card">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">
      <span class="ndx-explore-card__number">3</span>
      News section
    </h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      Recent news articles appear on the homepage. These are sample articles
      showing council announcements and updates.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-explore-card">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">
      <span class="ndx-explore-card__number">4</span>
      Footer links
    </h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      The footer contains links to Contact, Accessibility, Privacy, and other
      statutory pages that councils are required to provide.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

